commit.message: nemo-preview: remove po/ and fix gettext domain
nemo-image-converter: Remove po/
nemo-pastebin: remove po/

nemo-seahorse: remove po/

Also remove unused .desktop files
nemo-emblems: remove po/
nemo-compare: Remove po/
nemo-repair: Remove broken l10n framework and po/ dir
makepot: Remove the old potfile first.
l10n: Update POT
makepot: Fix scanning nemo-pastebin files in src/
Fix nemo-dropbox build
l10n: Update POT

l10n: Fix names and descriptions

names need to be simple and reflect the pkg names. They don't need
to be translated.

description on the other hand absolutely do. This commit fixes both.

python-nemo: provide nemo-python pkg name

Some packages (nemo-owncloud for instance) depend on nemo-python.
Debian's nemo-python conflicts with our own python-nemo so installing
nemo-owncloud results in the removal of python-nemo, which in turn
removes a whole bunch of extensions.

Work around this problem by providing the Debian stupid pkg name.

nemo-share: Fix incorrect gettext domain

The extension was looking into the gettext nemo-share domain
and picking up translations from its own po/ files, which were
obsolete.

Delete po/ and use cinnamon-translations' instead.
